@page "/attributes/stroke"
@using SvgBlazor.Docs.Components

<ExampleTitle>Stroke</ExampleTitle>
<p>The SvgStroke class is responsible for providing the paint of the outline of an svg element.</p>

<div><ExampleComponent ExampleCode="@(new StrokeBasicExample())" /></div>

<h5>DashArray</h5>
<p>To present stroke as a pattern of dashes and gaps, assign properly formatted string to DashArray property:</p>
<div><ExampleComponent ExampleCode="@(new StrokeDashArrayExample())" /></div>

<h5>DashOffset</h5>
<p>To render offset, assign value to DashOffset property. However, this will only work when DashArray is assigned as well:</p>
<div><ExampleComponent Height="25" ExampleCode="@(new StrokeDashOffsetExample())" /></div>

<h5>LineCap</h5>
<p>The following examples show how to define different stroke endings for open shapes:</p>
<div><ExampleComponent ExampleCode="@(new StrokeLineCapExamples())" /></div>

<h5>LineJoin</h5>
